Process loadNULISAseq output for downstream analysis

process_loadNULISAseq.Rd

This function takes the output from `loadNULISAseq` and performs additional processing and cleaning to prepare the data for downstream analysis (e.g., NAS). It standardizes sample and plate identifiers, cleans covariate names, and generates additional normalized and transformed data matrices.

Usage

process_loadNULISAseq(data)

Arguments

data

A list, the output from `loadNULISAseq` (from the NULISAseqR package), representing a single NULISAseq plate/run.

Value

A processed list with the following elements:

samples

A cleaned data frame of sample metadata, with standardized column names and identifiers.

covariateNames

A named character vector mapping cleaned covariate names to their original names.

Data_raw

Matrix of raw counts, with cleaned sample names.

Data_rawlog2

Matrix of log2-transformed raw counts, with cleaned sample names.

Data_IC

Matrix of IC-normalized data, with cleaned sample names.

Data_IClog2

Matrix of log2-transformed IC-normalized data, with cleaned sample names.

Data_Reverse

Matrix of IC-normalized data for reverse curve targets, with cleaned sample names.

Data_Reverselog2

Matrix of log2-transformed IC-normalized data for reverse curve targets, with cleaned sample names.

plateID

Character, standardized plate ID.

xmlFile

Character, xml file name.

ExecutionDetails

List of run/plate metadata.

numericCovariates

Character vector of numeric covariate names.

NPQ

Matrix of NPQ values, with cleaned sample names.

normed

List of normalized data.

normed_untransformedReverse

List of normalized data for reverse curve targets.

targets

Data frame of target information.

qcSample

Data frame of sample-level QC metrics.

qcPlate

Data frame of plate-level QC metrics.

aqParams

Data frame of AQ target parameters (if present).

detectability

List of target detectability for all samples and by sample group/matrix.

quantifiability

List of target quantifiability for all samples and by sample group/matrix (if AQ data present).

...

Other elements from the original input, as needed.

Details

- Removes unnecessary columns and standardizes identifiers for compatibility with downstream tools. - Cleans covariate (column) names to lowerCamelCase. - Adds or updates normalized and log2-transformed data matrices. - Used internally as a pre-processing step before merging or further analysis.

Examples

# processed <- process_loadNULISAseq(loadNULISAseq_output)
